# Script 8: FWDC Pedestrian Routing
# Full implementation of Fuzzy-Weighted Deterministic Closure
# Routes pedestrian accounting for traffic signal timing uncertainty
# Uses real-time catalysts (observed signal phases) to refine decisions

# Set routing origin and destination
position from lat=48.1351 lng=11.5656
position to lat=48.1400 lng=11.5750

# Configure FWDC algorithm
algorithm FWDC
mode pedestrian
walking_speed 1.4 m/s

# Load all prior data layers
load script 1 clocks
load script 2 isochrones
load script 3 weather
load script 4 towers
load script 5 devices
load script 6 signals airquality
load script 7 satellites

# Define fuzzy edge weights
edge weight = walk_time + signal_wait
signal_wait in [0, cycle_time]
resolution_floor beta_0 = min(cycle_times)

# Catalyst data sources (refine uncertainty)
catalyst signal camera at intersection
catalyst crowd density from mobile data
catalyst real-time signal broadcast
catalyst historical traffic patterns

# Compute route
fwdc compute path
optimize for travel_time
optimize for air_quality exposure
optimize for pedestrian safety

# Visualize routing
show optimal path on map
show alternative paths (faded)
show signal timing on path
show separation cost regions
show fuzzy intervals for critical decisions
show closure detection status

# Real-time adaptation
on signal phase observed: refine_interval
on crowd density update: recompute_safety
on weather change: adjust_speed

# Display results
route show
route metrics
separation costs show
catalyst effectiveness report
fwdc closure analysis
